            "id": "2bc9ab03506746109909e",
            "questionText": "Consider a regenerative braking system in a modern electric vehicle, where the traction motor works as a generator during braking. Using Faraday's law, the induced electromotive force (EMF) in the motor can be given by the formula $!$EMF = N \\cdot \\frac{\\Delta \\phi}{\\Delta t}$!$, where $!$N$!$ is the number of turns in the motor's coil and $!$\\frac{\\Delta \\phi}{\\Delta t}$!$ is the rate of change of magnetic flux through one coil. Calculate the numerical value of the induced EMF. Please provide the following values: the number of turns $!$N$!$ and the rate of change of magnetic flux $!$\\frac{\\Delta \\phi}{\\Delta t}$!$ (in Weber per second).",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
