            "questionText": "A loudspeaker's voice coil has a total active length of $!$L=0.5 \\text{ m}$!$ and is placed in a uniform magnetic field of magnitude $!$B=0.2 \\text{ T}$!$. If an electrical current of $!$I=0.3 \\text{ A}$!$ flows through the coil and the angle between the direction of the current and the magnetic field is $!$90^\\circ$!$, compute the magnitude of the force on the voice coil using the formula $!$F=I \\times L \\times B \\times \\sin \\theta$!$. Provide your answer in Newtons (N) as a single numerical value.",
